      "author_association" : "MEMBER",
      "body" : "It may be better to modify `CAutoFile` in that case. The file handle in the auto-file should[1] always be unique and pinned to a single thread, so I using `fread_unlocked` seems better, as it improves performance everywhere. (Though, it looks like `std::fread_unlocked` does not exist in C++, so I wonder if it exists on Windows and macOS?)\r\n\r\n[1] I may submit a related pull to better enforce this at compile-time.",
