      "author_association" : "MEMBER",
      "body" : "I tried to remove BufferedFile, but it seemed non-trivial. I think it is needed to recover from datadir corruption caused by previous releases of Bitcoin Core. I wonder how relevant this still is, and whether it is simpler to require those affected to re-do an IBD. Another small benefit would be that the fuzz timeout in `load_external_block_file` would likely be fixed, see https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/issues/28812#issuecomment-1807801984. (Attempting to read a block at every byte position of the file in a loop may be CPU and memory intensive)",
